race.comment: Tony Gollan's BARRELLING (15) did a bit of work after missing the kick then held on well for a close fourth to CHIEF IN CHARGE over this course and distance last start. Plummets in the weights and draws the inside alley. Great chance to return to winning ways. Stablemate BOOM SHOT (7) produced a real eye-catcher when fresh from a spell last time out, charging home late to be beaten under a length at this track and trip. Genuine galloper who will enjoy a nice trail behind a hot tempo and is going to be tough to hold out. CHIEF IN CHARGE (8) is in career-best form with back-to-back wins here at 1350m. Should get the run of the race from the favourable barrier and the hat trick is not out of reach. MEAN APPROACH (3) contested a Class 6 over today's journey here recently and wasn't beaten far. One of the key runners with Ryan Maloney taking over.
